      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gardner Will Carry U.S. Flag at Closing</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Bill Brink</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brink, Bill</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Greco Roman wrestler Rulon Gardner to carry flag for US at closing ceremonies at Sydney Olympics (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Rulon Gardner, whose victory over Aleksandr Karelin in Greco-Roman wrestling provided one of the biggest upsets of the Sydney Games, will carry the flag for the United States in today's closing ceremony.</p>
        <p>Gardner, a first-time Olympian who grew up on a farm in Wyoming, was elected by other American athletes. Each team nominates a candidate for flag bearer, and the athletes vote for one.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Rulon Gardner, whose victory over Aleksandr Karelin in Greco-Roman wrestling provided one of the biggest upsets of the Sydney Games, will carry the flag for the United States in today's closing ceremony.</p>
        <p>Gardner, a first-time Olympian who grew up on a farm in Wyoming, was elected by other American athletes. Each team nominates a candidate for flag bearer, and the athletes vote for one.</p>
        <p>''It all still shocks me,'' Gardner said. ''I'm numb about all of this. Now for me to carry the flag is also so incredible.''</p>
        <p>Last Wednesday, Gardner defeated the previously unbeaten Russian, Karelin, the three-time defending champion in the superheavyweight category.</p>
        <p>Bill Brink</p>
        <p>SYDNEY 2000: NOTEBOOK</p>
      </block>
